## sudo without pswd
     

     pet@girl:~$ sudo visudoer  #"vim /etc/sudoers" is dangerous
     

  now add one line
     

     pet ALL=(ALL)NOPASSWD: ALL
     

 now I can "sudo -i" without typing password

## Format disk 
 * check dev/
     

    $cd /dev
    $ls s-
     


 * plug mp3
     

    $ls s-
     

now i see a sdb is added here
 * umount
     
 
     umount /media/disk-1         //not always disk-1
     


 * then
     
 
     mkfs.vfat -I /dev/sdb
     

